{
  "texts": [
    "By using the all-MiniLM-L6-v2 model to generate text embeddings, and combining UMAP algorithm for dimensionality reduction and HDBSCAN algorithm for clustering, it calculated the coherence values between events to construct a high-level discrete structure narrative map.",
    "This framework supported analysts in incrementally refining the narrative model through semantic interactions, leading to a better understanding of the relationships between news events, as shown in Fig. 3 (1).",
    "These vector were used to generate the projection space and compute coherence.",
    "Another example is ADVISor [70](Fig. 3 (2)), which automatically generates annotated charts to answer natural language questions about tabular data based on BERT [75].",
    "Here, BERT encodes natural language questions and table headers into latent vectors."
  ]
}